            schema:text "The Soil Organic Matter Class classifies soil based on the amount and quality of organic matter it contains. Soils with high organic matter are usually fertile, retain moisture better, and support more biological activity. This classification helps in determining soil health and suitability for agricultural purposes. Source: Brady, N. C., & Weil, R. R. (2008). The Nature and Properties of Soils (14th ed.). Pearson Prentice Hall."@en ] ;
