soilvoc:CationExchangeCapacitySoil a skos:Concept,
        sosa:ObservableProperty ;
    skos:broader soilvoc:CationExchangeCapacity ;
    skos:definition [ dcterms:source glosis_cl:physioChemicalPropertyCode-CEC ;
            schema:text "CEC measures the soil’s ability to hold and exchange positively charged ions (cations). It is a critical indicator of soil fertility, as higher CEC values imply greater capacity to retain essential nutrients like calcium, magnesium, and potassium. Clayey and organic-rich soils typically exhibit higher CEC. Source: Soil Science Society of America."@en ] ;
    skos:exactMatch glosis_cl:physioChemicalPropertyCode-CEC ;
    skos:inScheme <https://soilwise-he.github.io/soil-vocabs> ;
